    "statementHTML": "<div class=\"statement-body\">\n<div class=\"statement-section statement-goal\">\n   <h2><span class=\"icon icon-goal\">&nbsp;</span><span>Goal </span></h2>\n   <span class=\"question-statement\">Given a positive integer <var>N</var>, perform the following operation repeatedly:<br><br>1. Reverse the digits of <var>N</var> to get <var>R</var>.<br><br>2. Add <var>N</var> + <var>R</var> to get a new number.<br><br>3. Replace <var>N</var> with this new number and repeat the process until <var>N</var> becomes a <strong>palindrome</strong>(a number that reads the same forwards and backwards) or until the <strong>step limit</strong> is reached.<br><br><strong>Step limit</strong>: 30 steps.<br><br><strong>Role</strong>: The step limit ensures the program does not run indefinitely for numbers that may never produce a palindrome within reasonable iterations. If the palindrome is not reached within 30 steps, the program should stop and print a specific message.</span>\n</div>\n<div class=\"statement-section statement-protocol\">\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Input</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-input\">A single integer <var>N</var>.</div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Output</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-output\">Two integers separated by a space: the resulting <strong>palindrome</strong> and the <strong>number of steps</strong> taken to reach it, unless the process is interrupted by a <strong>step limit</strong>.<br>If the <strong>step limit</strong> is exceeded before a <strong>palindrome</strong> is reached, print exactly: <const>Step limit reached</const></div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Constraints</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-constraints\">1 &le; <var>N</var> &le; 10,000</div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Example</div>\n      <div class=\"statement-inout\">\n         <div class=\"st